<TITLE> US gold futures hit $1,000/oz, first since Feb </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TOKYO Sep 8, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US gold futures hit $1,000 an ounce for the first time since February as the dollar's weakness, concerns about the sustainability of global economic recovery and worries about future inflation underpinned sentiment. Gold for December delivery touched $1,000, shortly after spot gold hit a six-month high above $997
